value.value: The lateral area of the two branches of a horseshoe-shaped mesenchymal swelling in the future nasal region of the embryo; it separates the olfactory pit from the developing eye and the ala of the nose/snout develops from it.

The central area of the two limbs of a horseshoe-shaped mesenchymal swelling that lie medial to the olfactory placode or pit in the future nasal region of the embryo; it joins with the ipsilateral maxillary prominence in the formation of half of the upper jaw, and the nasal tip and philtrum of the upper lip develop from it.

One of the system of communicating cavities in the brain that are continuous with the central canal of the spinal cord, that like it are derived from the medullary canal of the embryo, that are lined with an epithelial ependyma, and that contain a serous fluid.
The subdivision of the face that includes the eye (eyeball plus adnexa such as eyelids) and the orbit of the skull and associated parts of the face such as the eyebrows, if present.

One of the two jaw ridges either on the roof of the mouth between the upper teeth and the hard palate or on the bottom of the mouth behind the lower teeth[WP]. The alveolar ridges contain the sockets (alveoli) of the teeth[HP].
An internal pocketing of pharyngeal endoderm that contacts a region of ectoderm (a pharyngeal cleft) and interdigitates in the anterior and posterior directions with the pharyngeal arches.

definition.value: The pouches are polarized structures. For example, whereas the rostral half of each pouch expresses Bmp-7, the caudal half expresses FGF-8 and the dorsal aspect of each pouch is marked via its expression of Pax-1. each pouch has an individual sense of identity. Shh expression is a prominent early feature of the caudal endoderm of the second arch, and individual pouches mark the anterior limits of expression of Hox genes within the pharyngeal endoderm; Hox-a2 has a rostral boundary at the second pouch, Hox-a3 at the third pouch and Hox-a4 at the most caudal pouch[PMID:16313389]

value.value: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with the production and excretion of urine and those concerned with reproduction.

The layer of the myocardium composed of projections of contractile myocytes. The trabecular layer is bounded internally by the endocardium. In zebrafish, unlike the trabeculations of higher vertebrates, both atrial and ventricular trabeculae have more strut-like character, and are more uniform without apparent regional differences[ZFA].
In mammals, the proximal tubule is a nephron tubule that connects Bowman's capsule to the loop of Henle. It has a brush border epithelial morphology[GO].
The distal tubule is a nephron tubule that consists of the distal convoluted tubule and distal straight tubule segments.
An epithelial tube that will give rise to the mature heart.

The bulbus arteriosus is an elastic heart chamber[GO]. Multi-tissue structure that consists of three layers and through which the blood exits the heart. The bulbus arteriosus is a pear shaped chamber that functions as a capacitor, maintaining continuous blood flow into the gill arches[ZFA].
The region of the cerebral cortex covering the basal surface of the frontal lobes; this region normally controls emotion and decision making.
The glomerular endothelium is an epithelial tissue that covers the internal surfaces of the glomerulus.

label.value: loop of Henle ascending limb thin segment

value.value: A sub-portion of the loop of Henle in the nephron of the kidney that is permeable to ions but not to water.
Kidney pyramids are the conical arrangements of tubules that constitute the renal medulla in a multi-lobed mammalian kidney; they contain the loops of Henle and the medullary collecting ducts.
The cortical collecting duct is the portion of the collecting duct that resides in the renal cortex.
The small branching blood vessels in the kidney glomerulus that receives blood from the kidney afferent arterioles; these capillaries are under high pressure for filtering within the glomerulus.
A zone of skin that is part of a lower leg [Automatically generated definition].
Anatomical cluster that consists of all the skeletal elements (eg., bone, cartilage, and teeth) of the body.
One of a series of paired embryological vascular structures formed within a pharyngeal arch; in the adult, some of these vessels give rise to the great vessels[MP].
A transparent homogeneous acellular layer found between the substantia propria and the endothelial layer of the cornea[MP].

definition.value: The strong, resistant, thin, noncellular fourth layer of the cornea, located between the endothelium (from which it is secreted) and the stroma. (Cline et al., Dictionary of Visual Science, 4th ed)

value.value: A transparent homogeneous acellular layer, 6 to 9 um thick, lying between the basal lamina of the outer layer of stratified epithelium and the substantia propria of the cornea; it is considered to be a basement membrane.
One of three main pairs of arteries and their branches, which irrigate the cerebrum of the brain.
Mesopodial segment of the pes, including the tarsal skeleton and associated tissues.
Anatomical system that has as its parts the heart and blood vessels.

An artery of the systemic circulation, which is the part of the cardiovascular system which carries oxygenated blood away from the heart, to the body, and returns deoxygenated blood back to the heart.
An endothelium that lines the blood vasculature. Other endothelia may line lymph vessels, the heart.

The blood vessels that branch from the kidney interlobular artery, convey blood to the glomerular capillaries, and play an important role in the regulation of blood pressure as a part of the tubuloglomerular feedback mechanism.
The blood vessels that convey blood from the glomerulocapillary network to the capillary bed of the proximal convoluted tubule.
The epithelial lining of the luminal space of the urinary bladder.
The polygonal structure of the liver that consists of hepatocytes radiating outward from a hepatic vein.
A muscularis mucosa that is part of a esophagus.
The thin epithelium-like membrane composed of ependymal cells that lines the ventricular system of the brain and the spinal cord.
A stage that follows the blastula, gastrula and neurula stages. At the pharyngula stage, all vertebrate embryos show remarkable similarities.

In the blood supply of the kidney, the vasa recta renis (or straight arteries of kidney, or straight arterioles of kidney) form a series of straight capillaries in the medulla. They lie parallel to the loop of Henle. These vessels branch off the efferent arterioles of juxtamedullary nephrons (those nephrons closest to the medulla), enter the medulla, and surround the loop of Henle.
A basibranchial element that is bone. Basibranchial elements are ventral, median, and associated with a single pharyngeal arch in the pharyngeal arch 3-7 skeleton.
Dermal bone on the margin of the scapula. The cleithrum is attached to the skull in fishes, but free from the latter in amphibians and disappears early in the evolution of reptiles.
The dentary is a dermal bone that forms the antero-lateral part of the lower jaw in fishes and amphibians, extending to the whole lower jaw in mammals[VHOG,modified].
Paired, endochondral bones forming the anterior, and lateral walls of the otic capsules.
Organ consisting of skeletal tissue. Encompasses whole bones, fused bones, cartilaginious elements, teeth, dermal denticles.
Anatomical system that consists of all the joints of the body.
A mucosa that is part of a gastrointestinal system.

definition.value: The gut mucosa of amphioxus has insulin-secreting cells. http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16417468

value.value: An epithelium that is part of a uterine cervix [Automatically generated definition].
Any epithelium that lines one of the bile ducts.
An epithelium that is part of a intrahepatic bile duct [Automatically generated definition].
The thin layer of flat cells that line the aorta and form a barrier between circulating blood in the lumen and the rest of the vessel wall.
A vasculature that is part of a retina [Automatically generated definition].
The central region of trunk mesoderm. This tissue forms the notochord.
